swL3MgmtMIB.name: swL3MgmtMIB
swL3MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 3 Network Management Information for the proprietary enterprise.

swL3DevCtrlRIPState.name: swL3DevCtrlRIPState
swL3DevCtrlRIPState.description: This object indicates Routing Information Protocol (RIP) version 2 function is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlOSPFState.name: swL3DevCtrlOSPFState
swL3DevCtrlOSPFState.description: This object indicates OSPF protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState.name: swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState
swL3DevCtrlDVMRPState.description: This object indicates DVMRP protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlVrrpState.name: swL3DevCtrlVrrpState
swL3DevCtrlVrrpState.description: This object indicates VRRP protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlVrrpPingState.name: swL3DevCtrlVrrpPingState
swL3DevCtrlVrrpPingState.description: This object indicates VRRP protocol Ping is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlDHCPAutoConfigState.name: swL3DevCtrlDHCPAutoConfigState
swL3DevCtrlDHCPAutoConfigState.description: This object indicates auto config is enabled or disabled.

swL3DevCtrlPIMGlobalState.name: swL3DevCtrlPIMGlobalState
swL3DevCtrlPIMGlobalState.description: This object indicates PIM protocol is enabled or disabled.

swL3IpCtrlTable.name: swL3IpCtrlTable
swL3IpCtrlTable.description: This table contain IP interface information.

swL3IpCtrlEntry.name: swL3IpCtrlEntry
swL3IpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3IpCtrlIpAddr
swL3IpCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the interface. This object only can take the value of the unicast IP address.

swL3IpCtrlIfIndex.name: swL3IpCtrlIfIndex
swL3IpCtrlIfIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies the IP interface number in the swL3IpCtrlTable.

swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName
swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask.name: swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask
swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask.description: The IP net mask for this interface.

swL3IpCtrlVlanName.name: swL3IpCtrlVlanName
swL3IpCtrlVlanName.description: This object indicates the IP control entry's VLAN name. The VLAN name in each entry must be unique in the IP Control Table.

swL3IpCtrlMode.name: swL3IpCtrlMode
swL3IpCtrlMode.description: This object indicates the IP operation mode. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. manual(2) - the IP address will be set by manual. bootp(3) - the IP address will be set automatically from BOOTP server. dhcp(4) - the IP address will be set automatically from DHCP server.

swL3IpCtrlSecondary.name: swL3IpCtrlSecondary
swL3IpCtrlSecondary.description: When this is true(1) the IP address is the secondary IP. When false(2), the IP address is the primary IP.

swL3IpCtrlState.name: swL3IpCtrlState
swL3IpCtrlState.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3IpCtrlOperState.name: swL3IpCtrlOperState
swL3IpCtrlOperState.description: The current operational state of the IP interface.PS: Link state

swL3IpCtrlAdminState.name: swL3IpCtrlAdminState
swL3IpCtrlAdminState.description: The state of a specific IP interface.

swL3IpFdbInfoTable.name: swL3IpFdbInfoTable
swL3IpFdbInfoTable.description: A table that contains forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the switch in determining how to propagate the received IP packets.

swL3IpFdbInfoEntry.name: swL3IpFdbInfoEntry
swL3IpFdbInfoEntry.description: Information about a specific IP address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr.name: swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr
swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr.description: A IP address for which switch has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask.name: swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask
swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask.description: A IP net mask for this interface.for which switch has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoPort.name: swL3IpFdbInfoPort
swL3IpFdbInfoPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which packet having a IP address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that switch does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address.

swL3IpArpAgingTime.name: swL3IpArpAgingTime
swL3IpArpAgingTime.description: The timeout period in minutes for aging out dynamically learned arp information.

swL3IpStaticRouteTable.name: swL3IpStaticRouteTable
swL3IpStaticRouteTable.description: This entity's IP static Routing table.

swL3IpStaticRouteEntry.name: swL3IpStaticRouteEntry
swL3IpStaticRouteEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination, under a particular policy. Once an entry be built,it shouldn't be modified.That is,it just support create and delete action.

swL3IpStaticRouteDest.name: swL3IpStaticRouteDest
swL3IpStaticRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast (Class D) address value. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the swL3IpStaticRouteMask object is not equal to x.

swL3IpStaticRouteMask.name: swL3IpStaticRouteMask
swL3IpStaticRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the swL3IpStaticRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the swL3IpStaticRouteMask by reference to the IP Address Class. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the swL3IpStaticRouteDest object is not equal to swL3IpStaticRouteDest.

swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState.name: swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState
swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState.description: The routing state for this route.The value SHOULD be primary(1) or backup(2).

swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop.name: swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop
swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next sys- tem en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0.

swL3IpStaticRouteMetric.name: swL3IpStaticRouteMetric
swL3IpStaticRouteMetric.description: The routing metric for this route.

swL3IpStaticRouteStatus.name: swL3IpStaticRouteStatus
swL3IpStaticRouteStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3RelayBootpState.name: swL3RelayBootpState
swL3RelayBootpState.description: This object indicates DHCP Relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayBootpHopCount.name: swL3RelayBootpHopCount
swL3RelayBootpHopCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of router hops that the DHCP packets can cross.

swL3RelayBootpTimeThreshold.name: swL3RelayBootpTimeThreshold
swL3RelayBootpTimeThreshold.description: This object indicates the minimum time in seconds within which the switch must relay the DHCP request. If this time is exceeded, the switch will drop the BOOTP packet.

swL3RelayDhcpCtrlTable.name: swL3RelayDhcpCtrlTable
swL3RelayDhcpCtrlTable.description: This table specifys the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL3RelayDhcpCtrlEntry.name: swL3RelayDhcpCtrlEntry
swL3RelayDhcpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL3RelayDhcpCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3RelayDhcpCtrlInterfaceName
swL3RelayDhcpCtrlInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

swL3RelayDhcpCtrlState.name: swL3RelayDhcpCtrlState
swL3RelayDhcpCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3RelayDhcpOption82State.name: swL3RelayDhcpOption82State
swL3RelayDhcpOption82State.description: This object indicates DHCP Relay Option 82 function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDhcpOption82ChceckState.name: swL3RelayDhcpOption82ChceckState
swL3RelayDhcpOption82ChceckState.description: This object indicates DHCP Relay Option 82 Chceck function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDhcpOption82Policy.name: swL3RelayDhcpOption82Policy
swL3RelayDhcpOption82Policy.description: This object indicates DHCP Relay Option 82 Policy.

swL3RelayDnsState.name: swL3RelayDnsState
swL3RelayDnsState.description: This object indicates DNS Relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer.name: swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer
swL3RelayDnsPrimaryServer.description: This object indicates the address of the primary DNS server.

swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer.name: swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer
swL3RelayDnsSecondaryServer.description: This object indicates the address of the secondary DNS server.

swL3RelayDnsCacheState.name: swL3RelayDnsCacheState
swL3RelayDnsCacheState.description: This object indicates DNS Relay cache is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState.name: swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState
swL3RelayDnsStaticTableState.description: This object indicates DNS Relay static table is enabled or disabled.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable
swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable.description: This table display the current DNS relay static table.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry
swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry.description: A list of information display the current DNS relay static table.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName
swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName.description: The domain name of the entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr
swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlState.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlState
swL3RelayDnsCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.

swL3Md5Table.name: swL3Md5Table
swL3Md5Table.description: This table display the current MD5 key table.

swL3Md5Entry.name: swL3Md5Entry
swL3Md5Entry.description: A list of information display the current MD5 key table.

swL3Md5Key.name: swL3Md5Key
swL3Md5Key.description: An MD5 password of up to 16 bytes.

swL3Md5RowStatus.name: swL3Md5RowStatus
swL3Md5RowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3RouteRedistriTable.name: swL3RouteRedistriTable
swL3RouteRedistriTable.description: Route redistribution allows routers on the network. That are running different routing protocols to exchange routing information. This is accomplished by comparing the routes stored in the vairous routers routing tables and assinging appropriate metrics. This information is then exchanged among the various routers according to the individual routers current routing protocol.

swL3RouteRedistriEntry.name: swL3RouteRedistriEntry
swL3RouteRedistriEntry.description: A list of information display the route redistribution table.

swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol.name: swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol
swL3RouteRedistriSrcProtocol.description: Allows the selection of the protocol of the source device.

swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol.name: swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol
swL3RouteRedistriDstProtocol.description: Allows the selection of the protocol of the destination device.

swL3RouteRedistriType.name: swL3RouteRedistriType
swL3RouteRedistriType.description: Allows the selection of one of the methods for calcalculating the metric value.

swL3RouteRedistriMetric.name: swL3RouteRedistriMetric
swL3RouteRedistriMetric.description: Allows the entry of an OSPF interface cost. This is analogous to a Hop Count in the RIP routing protocol. The value '0' indicates default value.

swL3RouteRedistriRowStatus.name: swL3RouteRedistriRowStatus
swL3RouteRedistriRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL3OspfHostTable.name: swL3OspfHostTable
swL3OspfHostTable.description: The list of Hosts, and their metrics, that the router will advertise as host routes.

swL3OspfHostEntry.name: swL3OspfHostEntry
swL3OspfHostEntry.description: A metric to be advertised, for a given type of service, when a given host is reachable.

swL3OspfHostIpAddress.name: swL3OspfHostIpAddress
swL3OspfHostIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the Host.

swL3OspfHostTOS.name: swL3OspfHostTOS
swL3OspfHostTOS.description: The Type of Service of the route being configured.

swL3OspfHostAreaID.name: swL3OspfHostAreaID
swL3OspfHostAreaID.description: The Area the Host Entry is to be found within. By default, the area that a subsuming OSPF interface is in, or 0.0.0.0

swL3OspfHostStatus.name: swL3OspfHostStatus
swL3OspfHostStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

swL3ospfVirtIfTable.name: swL3ospfVirtIfTable
swL3ospfVirtIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.4 Virtual link parameters
swL3ospfVirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual inter- faces.

swL3ospfVirtIfEntry.name: swL3ospfVirtIfEntry
swL3ospfVirtIfEntry.description: Information about a single Virtual Interface.

swL3ospfVirtIfAreaId.name: swL3ospfVirtIfAreaId
swL3ospfVirtIfAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

swL3ospfVirtIfNeighbor.name: swL3ospfVirtIfNeighbor
swL3ospfVirtIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

swL3ospfVirtIfTransitDelay.name: swL3ospfVirtIfTransitDelay
swL3ospfVirtIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link- state update packet over this interface.

swL3ospfVirtIfRetransInterval.name: swL3ospfVirtIfRetransInterval
swL3ospfVirtIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state ad- vertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database descrip- tion and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round- trip time.

swL3ospfVirtIfHelloInterval.name: swL3ospfVirtIfHelloInterval
swL3ospfVirtIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the in- terface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

swL3ospfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: swL3ospfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval
swL3ospfVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neigh- bors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neigh- bor.

swL3ospfVirtIfEvents.name: swL3ospfVirtIfEvents
swL3ospfVirtIfEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this Virtual Link

swL3ospfVirtIfAuthType.name: swL3ospfVirtIfAuthType
swL3ospfVirtIfAuthType.description: The authentication type specified for a virtu- al interface. Additional authentication types may be assigned locally.

swL3ospfVirtIfAuthKey.name: swL3ospfVirtIfAuthKey
swL3ospfVirtIfAuthKey.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 9 The Interface Data Structure
swL3ospfVirtIfAuthKey.description: If Authentication Type is simplePassword, the device will left adjust and zero fill to 8 oc- tets. Note that unauthenticated interfaces need no authentication key, and simple password authen- tication cannot use a key of more than 8 oc- tets. Larger keys are useful only with authen- tication mechanisms not specified in this docu- ment.

swL3ospfVirtIfStatus.name: swL3ospfVirtIfStatus
swL3ospfVirtIfStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

swL3ospfIfTable.name: swL3ospfIfTable
swL3ospfIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters
swL3ospfIfTable.description: The OSPF Interface Table describes the inter- faces from the viewpoint of OSPF.

swL3ospfIfEntry.name: swL3ospfIfEntry
swL3ospfIfEntry.description: The OSPF Interface Entry describes one inter- face from the viewpoint of OSPF.

swL3ospfIfIpAddress.name: swL3ospfIfIpAddress
swL3ospfIfIpAddress.description: The IP address of this OSPF interface.

swL3ospfAddressLessIf.name: swL3ospfAddressLessIf
swL3ospfAddressLessIf.description: For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

swL3ospfIfAreaId.name: swL3ospfIfAreaId
swL3ospfIfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.

swL3ospfIfType.name: swL3ospfIfType
swL3ospfIfType.description: The OSPF interface type. By way of a default, this field may be intuited from the corresponding value of ifType. Broad- cast LANs, such as Ethernet and IEEE 802.5, take the value 'broadcast', X.25 and similar technologies take the value 'nbma', and links that are definitively point to point take the value 'pointToPoint'.

swL3ospfIfAdminStat.name: swL3ospfIfAdminStat
swL3ospfIfAdminStat.description: The OSPF interface's administrative status. The value formed on the interface, and the in- terface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPF.

swL3ospfIfRtrPriority.name: swL3ospfIfRtrPriority
swL3ospfIfRtrPriority.description: The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligi- ble to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their Router ID as a tie breaker.

swL3ospfIfTransitDelay.name: swL3ospfIfTransitDelay
swL3ospfIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link state update packet over this interface.

swL3ospfIfRetransInterval.name: swL3ospfIfRetransInterval
swL3ospfIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link-state ad- vertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database descrip- tion and link-state request packets.

swL3ospfIfHelloInterval.name: swL3ospfIfHelloInterval
swL3ospfIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the in- terface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

swL3ospfIfRtrDeadInterval.name: swL3ospfIfRtrDeadInterval
swL3ospfIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neigh- bors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

swL3ospfIfPollInterval.name: swL3ospfIfPollInterval
swL3ospfIfPollInterval.description: The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non- broadcast multi- access neighbor.

swL3ospfIfDesignatedRouter.name: swL3ospfIfDesignatedRouter
swL3ospfIfDesignatedRouter.description: The IP Address of the Designated Router.

swL3ospfIfBackupDesignatedRouter.name: swL3ospfIfBackupDesignatedRouter
swL3ospfIfBackupDesignatedRouter.description: The IP Address of the Backup Designated Router.

swL3ospfIfEvents.name: swL3ospfIfEvents
swL3ospfIfEvents.description: The number of times this OSPF interface has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

swL3ospfIfMulticastForwarding.name: swL3ospfIfMulticastForwarding
swL3ospfIfMulticastForwarding.description: The way multicasts should forwarded on this interface; not forwarded, forwarded as data link multicasts, or forwarded as data link uni- casts. Data link multicasting is not meaning- ful on point to point and NBMA interfaces, and setting ospfMulticastForwarding to 0 effective- ly disables all multicast forwarding.

swL3ospfIfDemand.name: swL3ospfIfDemand
swL3ospfIfDemand.description: Indicates whether Demand OSPF procedures (hel- lo supression to FULL neighbors and setting the DoNotAge flag on proogated LSAs) should be per- formed on this interface.

swL3ospfIfAuthType.name: swL3ospfIfAuthType
swL3ospfIfAuthType.description: The authentication type specified for an in- terface. Additional authentication types may be assigned locally.

swL3ospfIfAuthKey.name: swL3ospfIfAuthKey
swL3ospfIfAuthKey.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 9 The Interface Data Structure
swL3ospfIfAuthKey.description: The Authentication Key. If the Area's Author- ization Type is simplePassword, and the key length is shorter than 8 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. Note that unauthenticated interfaces need no authentication key, and simple password authen- tication cannot use a key of more than 8 oc- tets. Larger keys are useful only with authen- tication mechanisms not specified in this docu- ment. When read, ospfIfAuthKey always returns an Oc- tet String of length zero.

swL3ospfIfStatus.name: swL3ospfIfStatus
swL3ospfIfStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the en- try. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceTable.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceTable
swL3dvmrpInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's multicast- capable interfaces.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceEntry.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceEntry
swL3dvmrpInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dvmrpInterfaceTable. This row augments ipMRouteInterfaceEntry in the IP Multicast MIB, where the threshold object resides.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceIfIndex.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceIfIndex
swL3dvmrpInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which DVMRP is enabled.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceLocalAddress.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceLocalAddress
swL3dvmrpInterfaceLocalAddress.description: The IP address this system will use as a source address on this interface. On unnumbered interfaces, it must be the same value as dvmrpInterfaceLocalAddress for some interface on the system.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceMetric.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceMetric
swL3dvmrpInterfaceMetric.description: The distance metric for this interface which is used to calculate distance vectors.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceStatus.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceStatus
swL3dvmrpInterfaceStatus.description: The status of this entry. Creating the entry enables DVMRP on the virtual interface; destroying the entry or setting it to notInService disables DVMRP on the virtual interface.

swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadPkts.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadPkts
swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadPkts.description: The number of DVMRP packets received on the interface by the DVMRP process which were subsequently discarded as invalid (e.g. invalid packet format, or a route report from an unknown neighbor).

swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadRoutes.name: swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadRoutes
swL3dvmrpInterfaceRcvBadRoutes.description: The number of routes, in valid DVMRP packets, which were ignored because the entry was invalid.

swL3pimCbsrBootStrapPeriod.name: swL3pimCbsrBootStrapPeriod
swL3pimCbsrBootStrapPeriod.description: At the elected BSR, this is the interval between originating Bootstrap messages, and should be equal to 60 seconds.

swL3pimCbsrHashMaskLen.name: swL3pimCbsrHashMaskLen
swL3pimCbsrHashMaskLen.description: The length (in bits) of the mask to use in the hash function. For IPv4 we recommend a value of 30. For IPv6 we recommand a value of 126.

swL3pimCandidateRPHoldtime.name: swL3pimCandidateRPHoldtime
swL3pimCandidateRPHoldtime.description: For C-RPs, this is the Holdtime specified in C-RP-Adv message, and is used by the BSR to time out RPs. This should be set to 2.5 * [C-RP-Adv-Period]. Default: 150 seconds.

swL3pimCandidateRPPriority.name: swL3pimCandidateRPPriority
swL3pimCandidateRPPriority.description: The 'priority' of the included RP, for the corresponding Encoded-Group Address (if any), highest priority is '0' (i.e. the lower the value of the 'Priority' field, the higher the priority). This field is stored at the BSR upon receipt along with the RP address and corresponding Encoded-Group Address.

swL3pimCandidateRPWildcardPrefixCnt.name: swL3pimCandidateRPWildcardPrefixCnt
swL3pimCandidateRPWildcardPrefixCnt.description: The number of enocded group addresses included in the message; indicating the group prefixes for which the C-RP is advertising. A Prefix-Cnt of '0' implies a prefix of 224.0.0.0 with mask length of 4; i.e. all multicast groups. If the C-RP is not configured with Group-prefix information, the C-RP puts a default value of '0' in this field.

swL3pimLastHopSptThreshold.name: swL3pimLastHopSptThreshold
swL3pimLastHopSptThreshold.description: Specifies a last hop router threshold.

swL3pimRegChksumIncDataTable.name: swL3pimRegChksumIncDataTable
swL3pimRegChksumIncDataTable.description: The PIM Register Checksum Including Data Table contains the PIM register checksum including data information, like RP address and state.

swL3pimRegChksumIncDataEntry.name: swL3pimRegChksumIncDataEntry
swL3pimRegChksumIncDataEntry.description: An entry in the PIM Register Checksum Including Data Table.

swL3SwL3pimRegChksumIncDataState.name: swL3SwL3pimRegChksumIncDataState
swL3SwL3pimRegChksumIncDataState.description: The state of register checksum including data for RPs.

swL3pimRegisterProbeTime.name: swL3pimRegisterProbeTime
swL3pimRegisterProbeTime.description: When null Registers are used, this is the time between sending a null Register and the Register-Suppression-Timer expiring unless it is restarted by receiving a Register-Stop. Thus, a null Register would be sent when the Register-Suppression-Timer reaches this value. Default: 5 seconds.

swL3pimRegisterSuppressionTime.name: swL3pimRegisterSuppressionTime
swL3pimRegisterSuppressionTime.description: This is the mean interval between receiving a Register-Stop and allowing Registers to be sent again. A lower value means more frequent register bursts at RP, while a higher value means longer join latency for new receiver. Default: 60 seconds.

swL3pimInfoTable.name: swL3pimInfoTable
swL3pimInfoTable.description: The PIM Information Table contains the PIM related information, like DR priority.

swL3pimInfoEntry.name: swL3pimInfoEntry
